I'm late.

513
01:04:38,818 --> 01:04:40,322
Hey.

514
01:04:42,795 --> 01:04:44,972
I'll be out the back from midnight on.

515
01:04:45,690 --> 01:04:47,869
Call or text if things get ugly, okay?

516
01:05:09,550 --> 01:05:11,509
Oh, Chloe!

517
01:05:12,647 --> 01:05:14,107
Person I was looking to see.

518
01:05:14,695 --> 01:05:15,988
Hi, Morris.

519
01:05:16,664 --> 01:05:18,073
How are you this evening?

520
01:05:19,134 --> 01:05:20,811
I'm well, how about yourself?

521
01:05:20,849 --> 01:05:22,267
I'm great.

522
01:05:23,337 --> 01:05:26,620
Zane did enlighten you about
our little deal, right?

523
01:05:28,405 --> 01:05:29,698
He sure did.

524
01:05:31,641 --> 01:05:36,065
Because I would like to redeem one
of those coupons tonight.

525
01:05:36,874 --> 01:05:40,358
That is as long as you are not too busy?

526
01:05:42,572 --> 01:05:44,166
No, Morris, I'm not.

527
01:05:44,846 --> 01:05:46,263
That's great.

528
01:05:47,455 --> 01:05:50,875
Why don't you join me in my office?

529
01:05:55,420 --> 01:05:58,464
Sure, why don't I fix you
a drink at the bar first?

530
01:05:59,175 --> 01:06:00,702
It's a marvelous idea.

531
01:06:01,288 --> 01:06:03,932
How about a vermouth straight up?

532
01:06:07,822 --> 01:06:08,536
Sure.

533
01:06:09,792 --> 01:06:10,925
See you in a few.

534
01:06:59,373 --> 01:07:00,655
Hey, Chloe.

535
01:07:00,680 --> 01:07:01,950
Hi, Morris.

536
01:07:01,975 --> 01:07:03,208
How are you doing?

537
01:07:04,780 --> 01:07:06,305
Doing well.

538
01:07:09,822 --> 01:07:12,158
We missed you last weekend at the club.

539
01:07:13,391 --> 01:07:14,509
I know.

540
01:07:15,514 --> 01:07:18,781
Yeah, the regulars,
they get a little testy...

541
01:07:19,072 --> 01:07:21,783
...when they don't get their usual
pick of the litter.

542
01:07:22,178 --> 01:07:23,929
I bet.

543
01:07:26,389 --> 01:07:28,475
You know, honey,

544
01:07:29,390 --> 01:07:31,767
if you work your cards right,

545
01:07:32,011 --> 01:07:35,890
I'm just gonna have to make you
a dancer at the new club.

546
01:07:36,945 --> 01:07:41,074
And you'll be making three times
the money you are making right now.

547
01:07:43,101 --> 01:07:48,524
Because I do know talent.

548
01:07:51,315 --> 01:07:53,902
Well, thank you, Morris. I'm flattered.

549
01:07:54,872 --> 01:07:57,552
Why don't I get you your drink
I made for you.

550
01:08:00,303 --> 01:08:03,753
Did you spill honey? That's okay,
I didn't need that drink anyway.

551
01:08:03,961 --> 01:08:05,921
Because, you know,

552
01:08:07,967 --> 01:08:12,676
I knew that you had the talent...

553
01:08:13,364 --> 01:08:17,595
...that every man should experience.

554
01:08:17,845 --> 01:08:20,565
Why don't we both get ourselves a drink?

555
01:08:20,590 --> 01:08:23,250
Because I don't want a drink.
I don't need a drink.

556
01:08:23,350 --> 01:08:28,127
I am ready to experience...

557
01:08:29,084 --> 01:08:34,758
...all the good things that I'm sure
that you are capable of doing.

558
01:08:36,803 --> 01:08:43,232
So, I think we should just go on upstairs
and get to know each other a little bit.

559
01:08:45,493 --> 01:08:47,414
Morris, I insist.

560
01:08:47,614 --> 01:08:49,147
Well, Chloe,

561
01:08:50,387 --> 01:08:56,184
I really am done with the small talk
and fucking around...

562
01:08:56,488 --> 01:09:03,100
...because it's time to go fuck.

563
01:12:02,502 --> 01:12:06,691
No, no, no, Chloe.

564
01:12:06,914 --> 01:12:09,204
Chloe? Babe?

565
01:12:09,229 --> 01:12:12,432
Wake up. Babe, wake up!

566
01:12:12,693 --> 01:12:15,948
Wake up! Wake up, Chloe!

567
01:12:16,107 --> 01:12:19,068
Come on baby, wake up Chloe!

568
01:12:19,664 --> 01:12:20,873
Chloe, wake up!

569
01:12:21,716 --> 01:12:25,509
Wake up, Chloe! Hey, babe. Wake up!

570
01:12:26,837 --> 01:12:28,694
Wake up, baby.

571
01:12:30,238 --> 01:12:33,870
Wake up, Chloe, wake up.

572
01:13:04,481 --> 01:13:05,574
Zane!

573
01:13:09,454 --> 01:13:10,655
What are you gonna do, Zane?

574
01:13:10,663 --> 01:13:12,374
Liliy! Not now!

575
01:13:15,297 --> 01:13:19,551
Where are the matches, huh?
Where the fuck are my matches?

576
01:13:19,892 --> 01:13:23,484
Zane, the doctors said you ain't
supposed to smoke in the house, remember?

577
01:13:23,509 --> 01:13:25,065
I don't have time for this right now.

578
01:13:25,090 --> 01:13:26,842
Well, then answer me, damn it.

579
01:13:27,615 --> 01:13:28,492
Don't tell me what to do.

580
01:13:30,956 --> 01:13:32,022
Why don't you listen to me?

581
01:13:35,526 --> 01:13:37,836
Don't you get feisty with me here, okay?

582
01:13:37,861 --> 01:13:40,280
I told you I don't have time
for this right now.

583
01:13:41,547 --> 01:13:42,941
I gotta get to work.

584
01:13:43,630 --> 01:13:46,079
Working a double shift,
we'll talk about it later.

585
01:13:48,925 --> 01:13:51,120
Zane?
What?

586
01:13:54,586 --> 01:13:57,548
Do you still love me?

587
01:17:09,975 --> 01:17:11,810
So, what's your big problem?

588
01:17:12,064 --> 01:17:14,966
Morris, I need to talk to you about Chloe.

589
01:17:15,105 --> 01:17:16,189
What about her?

590
01:17:16,686 --> 01:17:20,357
She is not doing well,
she is in a real bad shape.

591
01:17:21,352 --> 01:17:22,895
I want to strike a deal, Morris.

592
01:17:23,915 --> 01:17:26,125
What?
I need to renegotiate.

593
01:17:26,432 --> 01:17:31,758
Zane, you know in my book
that a deal is a deal.

594
01:17:31,830 --> 01:17:34,291
And when it's done, it's done.

595
01:17:34,835 --> 01:17:37,588
I've made a big mistake.

596
01:17:37,669 --> 01:17:39,337
It wasn't Chloe on the website.

597
01:17:39,692 --> 01:17:43,155
What are you talking about
it wasn't Chloe for God's sake.

598
01:17:43,180 --> 01:17:45,402
I mean it just wasn't, okay?

599
01:17:46,514 --> 01:17:49,623
It was her sister.
She died a few months ago.

600
01:17:50,272 --> 01:17:53,675
And I need Chloe to be out of this.

601
01:17:56,637 --> 01:17:58,384
That's not gonna happen, Zane.

602
01:18:01,124 --> 01:18:04,978
Listen, Morris, I already
work double shifts for you,

603
01:18:05,498 --> 01:18:08,681
you can keep that out of my wages,
keep my tips, I'll do anything Morris,

604
01:18:08,706 --> 01:18:11,000
but I need Chloe out of our deal.

605
01:18:12,210 --> 01:18:14,832
I don't know if we can do that, Zane.

606
01:18:18,289 --> 01:18:21,309
Morris, please.

607
01:18:32,725 --> 01:18:35,794
I brought the only thing
that has value in my life.

608
01:18:47,872 --> 01:18:53,654
I was married once.
Someone I loved very much.

609
01:18:59,290 --> 01:19:02,183
Zane, I don't even think it would cover
half of what you owe me though.

610
01:19:03,144 --> 01:19:05,639
I know, but like I said
I'll work off the rest.

611
01:19:10,655 --> 01:19:14,520
Listen, Morris, everyone
deserves a second chance.

612
01:19:22,841 --> 01:19:25,260
All right, Zane.

613
01:19:32,756 --> 01:19:35,301
Oh, hell.

614
01:19:38,953 --> 01:19:41,290
I suppose...

615
01:19:46,163 --> 01:19:47,990
I suppose so.

616
01:19:53,908 --> 01:19:55,643
Zane...

617
01:19:57,582 --> 01:19:59,082
Goddamn it.

618
01:20:00,192 --> 01:20:02,896
If I let you off the hook on this,

619
01:20:05,346 --> 01:20:07,658
you have to understand,

620
01:20:09,826 --> 01:20:11,482
this is a one time deal.

621
01:20:11,968 --> 01:20:14,102
Do you understand that?
Yes, Morris, I understand that.

622
01:20:14,142 --> 01:20:16,043
I promise I'll never
get in this deep again.

623
01:20:16,494 --> 01:20:17,818
All right.

624
01:20:21,448 --> 01:20:24,054
You work off what you owe me.

625
01:20:27,027 --> 01:20:29,355
And when that is done,

626
01:20:31,511 --> 01:20:34,473
Chloe is free and clear.

627
01:20:50,479 --> 01:20:52,230
Goddamn it.

628
01:20:53,706 --> 01:20:56,987
You remind me so much of him.

629
01:20:59,998 --> 01:21:03,228
And I can't believe what I'm about to do.

630
01:21:09,779 --> 01:21:14,867
You know, Zane, I had a son once.

631
01:21:21,458 --> 01:21:23,913
And he looked so much like you.

632
01:21:27,227 --> 01:21:29,007
So much.

633
01:21:36,628 --> 01:21:39,688
He was killed in a car accident.

634
01:21:42,626 --> 01:21:45,444
I want you to take this.

635
01:21:47,081 --> 01:21:49,360
And I want you to take Chloe...

636
01:21:50,348 --> 01:21:55,061
...and I want you guys to go
and start a new life, away from here.

637
01:22:00,780 --> 01:22:02,941
He loved that car.

638
01:22:05,453 --> 01:22:08,071
That car was supposed to be...

639
01:22:12,739 --> 01:22:15,492
...his 21st birthday present.

640
01:22:18,546 --> 01:22:20,721
He never got it, Zane.

641
01:22:25,919 --> 01:22:27,879
So, trust me on this one.

642
01:22:32,123 --> 01:22:34,417
This is my second chance.

643
01:22:37,343 --> 01:22:40,333
So, don't fuck it up for me, all right?

644
01:22:43,051 --> 01:22:45,345
Now get out of here.

645
01:22:52,173 --> 01:22:55,218
You take care, son.

